en media, and thus the expanding range of comparative literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aArt and literaturevCongresses. 0aComic books, strips, etc.xHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aComparative literaturevCongresses. 0aLiteraturexAdaptationsvCongresses. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh  aAdaptation.  acomics studies.  aintermediality.  aworld literature.1 aAbaï-Ringgenberg, Andia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlmond, Adile Aslan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArbex, Márcia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsk Nunes, Denise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaptista do Lago, Izabela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoissieu, Michel de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchenberger, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBürger-Koftis, Michaela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConcilio, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorrêa Prando, Fabiana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCunha, Maria Zilda da, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeTora, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEchiffre, Capucine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsteves Pereira, Margarida, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb